data.title: Offenbach 2) Main
meta_keywords: Meyers Gazetteer of the German Empire
data.meta_description: The historical entry for Offenbach, Starkenburg, Hessen, including parish and jurisdiction information, in the Meyers Gazetteer of the German Empire also known as Meyers Orts- und Verkehrs-Lexikon des Deutschen Reichs.
data.text:
Type KrSt. - Offenbach is a Kreisstadt (County Seat).

Lvl I Hessen - Level I shows which Kingdom or State the place is located in. Offenbach is located in Hessen.

Prov Starkenburg - The Province shows which Province or State the place is located in. Offenbach is located in Starkenburg.

LG Darmstadt - The Landgericht for Offenbach is in Darmstadt. The Landgericht is where the District Court is located.

BKdo Darmstadt - The Bezirkskommando for Offenbach is in Darmstadt. The Bezirkskommando is the District Military Command. You can look in the BKdo to find military records.

AG Offenbach 2) Main [self] - The Amtsgericht for Offenbach is in Offenbach 2) Main [self]. The Amtsgericht is where the Lower District Court is located.

StdA Offenbach 2) Main [self] - The Standesamt for Offenbach is in itself. The Standesamt is where the Civil Registration Office is located.

kath. Pfk. 5 - Offenbach has 5 katholisch Pfarrkirche (Catholic parish churches).

ev. Pfk. 2 - Offenbach has 2 evangelisch Pfarrkirche (Protestant parish churches).

Syn 1 - Offenbach has 1 Synagoge (Synagogue).

Other 2 - Offenbach has 2 churches that are not an evangelical church, Catholic church, or Synagogue.
